{
  "stem": "6258.7",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There, I was in care of [GERMAN]-- of the files of the people who had been sent already to gas.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And people who were already in that evidence of that camp-- any camp, because Gross-Rosen or something, and came there, they came with their files.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We also came with our files-- Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But then, when I had to look into that [GERMAN] where, for example, when there was a transport coming from, I don't know, Turkey or Hungary or something, it was only written, '4,000 people' or '3,000 people' [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I noticed there was a part of cards, and this was the transport from Plaszow, and there was my father.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I found my father's card there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And therefore, I know exactly when he was [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So I was working there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then I had another--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was November.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was November '44.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Oh, the date of my father?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was sometimes 15 that [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1944.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sometime October.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Until the end in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Birkenau, it was part of Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We were about two weeks in Birkenau, perhaps.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Auschwitz till 18th of January.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When Krakau was already-- 1945.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so there, I was witnessing also, just at the beginning of January, the execution of the four Jewish girls who were supplying the sonderkommando with dynamite for the revolt of that sonderkommando who was working in the crematorium, and they sprang with dynamite.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Successfully.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this crematorium-- and maybe this was also the reason that we went to work, and we were staying alive from Plaszow, because there was the largest crematorium didn't exist.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they had such a backlog of dead people that they couldn't do it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The girls were working at the munitions factory in Monowitz in one of these Auschwitz camps.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
